17/12/2006
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Spain reaffirmed on Saturday (December 16th) that it would restrict the access of workers from Bulgaria and Romania to its labour market for two years after the two Balkan countries' accession to the EU on January 1st, 2007. The confirmation came during separate visits by the Spanish Interior Minister Alfredo Perez Rubalcaba and Minister of Labour and Social Affairs Jesus Caldera Sanchez-Capitan to Sofia and Bucharest on Saturday.
In other news, Bulgarian Foreign Minister Ivaylo Kalfin left Saturday on a several-day visit to the United States. He will stay there until Thursday for talks with senior US government and business representatives, including US Secretary of State Condoleezza Rice. (Monitor - 17/12/06; BTA, BNR, Mediafax - 16/12/06)
